@startuml "Complete Data Flow Pipeline"
title "Infraware Terminal: Complete Data Flow from User Input to Output"

' ==================== MAIN FLOW ====================

node "User Input" as user_input
node "EventHandler\npoll_event()" as event_poll

node "TerminalState\nupdate" as state_update
node "InputBuffer\ninsert_char()" as input_buffer

node "InputClassifier\nclassify()" as classifier

node "Alias Expansion\nCommandCache" as alias_expand

node "SCAN Chain\n10 Handlers" as scan_chain

node "InputType\nResult" as input_type

' Command path
node "CommandOrchestrator\nhandle_command()" as cmd_orch

node "CommandExecutor\nexecute()" as executor

node "CommandOutput\n{stdout,stderr,exit_code}" as cmd_output

node "TerminalState\nadd_output()" as state_output_cmd

node "TerminalUI\nrender()" as render_cmd

' NL path
node "NaturalLanguageOrchestrator\nhandle_query()" as nl_orch

node "LLMClient\nquery()" as llm_client

node "LLM Response" as llm_response

node "ResponseRenderer\nrender()" as renderer

node "TerminalState\nadd_output()" as state_output_nl

node "TerminalUI\nrender()" as render_nl

' Final output
node "Terminal Display\n(Ratatui)" as display

' ==================== DATA FLOW ====================

' User input flow
user_input --> event_poll : keyboard input
event_poll --> state_update : TerminalEvent
state_update --> input_buffer : InputChar(c)
input_buffer --> state_update : char inserted

' Input classification
state_update --> classifier : on Submit

classifier --> alias_expand : extract first word
alias_expand --> classifier : expanded input

classifier --> scan_chain : classify_internal()
scan_chain --> input_type : Some(InputType)

' Command execution
input_type --> cmd_orch : InputType::Command
cmd_orch --> executor : execute(cmd, args)
executor --> cmd_output : CommandOutput
cmd_output --> state_output_cmd : format output
state_output_cmd --> render_cmd : updated TerminalState

' Natural language
input_type --> nl_orch : InputType::NaturalLanguage
nl_orch --> llm_client : query(text)
llm_client --> llm_response : LLM response
llm_response --> renderer : format response
renderer --> state_output_nl : formatted String
state_output_nl --> render_nl : add_output()

' Rendering
render_cmd --> display : ratatui::draw()
render_nl --> display : ratatui::draw()

display --> user_input : user sees output

' ==================== CACHE INTEGRATION ====================

node "CommandCache\n{available, unavailable, aliases}" as cmd_cache

classifier -.-> cmd_cache : is_alias?
cmd_cache -.-> classifier : expansion

scan_chain -.-> cmd_cache : verify command
cmd_cache -.-> scan_chain : exists?

executor -.-> cmd_cache : command_exists?
cmd_cache -.-> executor : cached result

' ==================== PATTERN COMPILATION ====================

node "CompiledPatterns\nGlobal LazyLock<>" as patterns

scan_chain -.-> patterns : has_shell_operators()?
patterns -.-> scan_chain : regex match

scan_chain -.-> patterns : has_command_syntax()?
scan_chain -.-> patterns : has_natural_language()?

' ==================== HISTORY EXPANSION ====================

node "CommandHistory\n(entries, position)" as history

node "HistoryExpansionHandler\n(H2 in chain)" as history_handler

state_update -.-> history : history_previous()
history -.-> state_update : previous entry

classifier -.-> history_handler : classify

history_handler -.-> history : access history
history -.-> history_handler : expanded input

' ==================== LEGEND & NOTES ====================

note right of user_input
  **Input Entry Point**
  - Keyboard characters
  - Meta keys (Enter, Tab, Arrows)
  - Window resize events
end note

note right of event_poll
  **Event Polling**
  - Crossterm event reader
  - Windows: filter Press events only
  - Timeout: 100ms (responsive loop)
end note

note right of scan_chain
  **SCAN Algorithm**
  1. Empty input
  2. History expansion (!!,  !$, !^, !*)
  3. Application builtins (clear, reload-*)
  4. Shell builtins (., :, [, [[, export)
  5. Path commands (./script.sh)
  6. Known commands (60+ DevOps)
  7. Command syntax (flags, pipes)
  8. Typo detection (Levenshtein ≤2)
  9. Natural language (heuristics)
  10. Default handler (fallback)

  Performance: <100μs average
end note

note right of executor
  **Command Execution**
  - Async via tokio::process
  - Timeout: 5 minutes (configurable)
  - Output capture: UTF-8 parsing
  - Interactive detection: suspend/resume
end note

note right of llm_client
  **LLM Backends**
  - MockLLMClient: dev/testing
  - HttpLLMClient: production
  - Timeout: 30 seconds
  - Streaming: M2 enhancement
end note

note right of renderer
  **Response Formatting**
  - Markdown parsing
  - Syntax highlighting (256-color ANSI)
  - Code block detection
  - Header/list formatting
end note

note right of display
  **Terminal Rendering**
  - Ratatui framework
  - Layout: Header/Output/Input
  - Colors: 256-color ANSI
  - Cursor: at input position
  - Refresh rate: tied to event polling
end note

note bottom
  **Complete Pipeline Summary**

  Linear Flow:
  1. User types character(s) and presses Enter
  2. EventHandler polls crossterm and returns TerminalEvent
  3. TerminalState updates InputBuffer with characters
  4. On Submit: classifier.classify(input)
  5. Alias expansion via CommandCache
  6. SCAN chain: 10 handlers process input
  7. Returns InputType (Command, NL, Typo, or Empty)
  8. Route to orchestrator (Command or NL)
  9. Execute and get output
  10. Format output via ResponseRenderer (if NL)
  11. Add to TerminalState.output
  12. TerminalUI renders complete state
  13. Ratatui draws to terminal screen
  14. Loop back to step 1

  Caching Layers:
  - CompiledPatterns: LazyLock<RegexSet>
  - CommandCache: LazyLock<RwLock<CommandCache>>
  - KnownCommandHandler: whitelist with PATH verification

  Thread Safety:
  - Arc<RwLock<Vec<String>>> for history_arc
  - RwLock<CommandCache> with poisoning recovery
  - All handlers: Send + Sync traits

  Performance Optimizations:
  - Fast paths first (empty, history)
  - Precompiled regex (10-100x speedup)
  - Short-circuit evaluation
  - Cached command availability checks
  - Async execution with timeouts
end note

@enduml
